Please follow the following steps:

1.) First download and install Django from here: 

https://www.djangoproject.com/download/

2.) Rename the directory to 'teammetrics' if it is anything else.

3.) Then go to the teammetrics directory and run:
[You should be in /.../teammetrics$]

python manage.py syncdb
python manage.py runserver

4.) Open your browser and go to:

http://127.0.0.1:8000

5.) To view the admin enter the following details:

Username: divyanshu
Password: 123456

Latest Modification:
Added the 'add team to metrics' function.
Added the admin menu for modifying the data on the new teams, and also for updating the data on the present teams.

===Adding a new Team===
After starting the server go to add-new-team or alternatively go here: http://127.0.0.1:8000/add/
Fill the team name and the contributors, add new fields if required, the click on COMMIT.

===Adding data to the new team===
After starting the server, go to admin or alternatively go here: http://127.0.0.1:8000/admin/
Enter the details provided above.
Click on the team you have just added. On the right side there will be a 'Add team_name' button, click on it.
Add the data to the team.

Written by Divyanshu Verma

